it‚Äôs not only the high concentration of incredibly skilled professionals\nthat gather in this remote location in northern Germany that provides so much\nvalue to me."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"It‚Äôs the Newbies as well."}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"It might not be obvious to you as a first-time attendee or if you are new to the\nfield of professional software development: "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"you have something to contribute,\ntoo!"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Since 2016, tickets for the SoCraTes are raffled and this provides a much higher\ninflux of participants which haven‚Äôt attended any conference before that focuses\non software as a craft. If you are one of those, I‚Äôd like to encourage you to\noffer a session, ask for support on a topic (this is called a "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"pull session"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"),\nand not to hesitate to offer your opinion during other sessions."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Because your are adding value, even by asking a question!"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Your "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"How?"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" questions are making us better teachers. Being a Software\nCraftsperson one of the most important goals is to become great at explaining\nthe value of certain behaviour or technique. Because we loathe dogmatic\napplication of \"best practices\" but strive for developing an understanding of\nthe underlying principles of software development, so we can find the best\nsolution for a problem, not the most obvious one. We can‚Äôt expect this from our\npeers, if we fail to explain it to them."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Your "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Why?"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" questions are making us more effective. There are many biases that\nfavor repeating decisions that have worked in the past, but in a chaotic market\nthis strategy of our mind is not always a good fit. Being confronted with an\nhonest question about the reasons for a certain decision forces us the make our\noftentimes only implicitly known reasons and assumptions that lead to that\ndecision explicit. It‚Äôs very helpful to shake one's belief system openly once in\na while, because we are then challenged to do this honestly."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"You get to do all what's mentioned above (offering knowledge, asking questions,\nchallenging decisions) in a safe environment which is very unique to the\nSoftware Craft Community: everybody understands that there is never only one\ngood solution to a problem, because in Software everything "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"depends"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":". Therefore\nyou will never hear someone dismissing an idea as wrong, even if their own idea\nabout it is highly controversial to what they are presented."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"They will offer their advice and experience in a non judgemental way. And that‚Äôs\nwhy the SoCraTes and this community is awesome "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"for Software Craftspeople of\nevery skill level"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"type":"root","data":{"quirksMode":false}},"frontmatter":{"title":"Bring your inexperience to a conference","subtitle":"On contributing to a community","noheadline":null,"date":"2017-04-23T13:00+02:00","abstract":"As a newbie you have something to contribute to a conference as well!\n","lang":null},"headings":[]}},"Footer":{"id":"cfe5b9e2-511c-5615-992a-dab82e1f8ed7","name":"Footer","relativeDirectory":"","relativePath":"Footer.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Nordic Semiconductor"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://nordicsemi.com/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"."},{"children":[],"tagName":"br","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\nMentor. Speaker. Conference & Community builder. Camper. üèïÔ∏è üöê"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-